  <h1>Turbo Frame Examples</h1>
  <p>The following sections are basic examples on how to use Turbo. For more details, see <a href="https://turbo.hotwired.dev/handbook/introduction">the documentation</a>.</p>
</header>
<main>
  <hr />
  <section>
    <header>
      <h2>Turbo-frame default usage: links</h2>
      <p>Wrap a block with the <code>turbo-frame</code> tag, have your response return the same tag and id and refresh parts of your DOM, no JS required.</p>
    </header>

    <turbo-frame id="case1">
      <a href="/case1"><b>Click me!</b></a>
    </turbo-frame>
  </section>

  <hr />
  <section>
    <header>
      <h2>Turbo-frame default usage: forms</h2>
      <p>Wrap a form in a <code>turbo-frame</code> tag and the response of submitting the form will replace the frame. Redirects are followed.</p>
    </header>

    <turbo-frame id="form">
      <form method="post">
        <label for="post[name]">Your name</label>
        <input name="post[name]" type="text" />
        <button type="submit">Submit</button>
      </form>
    </turbo-frame>
  </section>

  <hr />
  <section>
    <header>
      <h2>Target a turbo-frame</h2>
      <p>Add <code>data-turbo-frame</code> to load the response into a <code>turbo-frame</code> somewhere else on the DOM.</p>
    </header>

    <a href="/case2" data-turbo-frame="case2"><b>Load content in following box</b></a> <br />
    <aside>
      <turbo-frame id="case2">
        <progress id="progress-bar" aria-label="Content loadingâ€¦"></progress>
      </turbo-frame>
    </aside>
  </section>

  <hr />
  <section>
    <header>
      <h2>Drive with caching example</h2>
      <p>With Turbo Drive enabled, all page transitions are cached (and with Turbo 8, hovered links are preloaded). So visiting a page a second time will load from cache, not the server.</p>
    </header>

    <a href="/drive-caching">Go to page 2</a>
  </section>

  <hr />
  <section>
    <header>
      <h2>Overriding targets</h2>
      <p>Responses can override targets</p>
    </header>

    <turbo-frame id="messages" target="_top">
      <a href="/messages/1"> Following link will replace the whole page, not this frame. </a><br />

      <a href="/messages/1" data-turbo-frame="_self">
        Following link will replace just this frame.
      </a>
    </turbo-frame>
  </section>

  <hr />
  <section>
    <header>
      <h2>Experiment: return 2 frames</h2>
    </header>
    <turbo-frame id="frame1">
      <aside>
        <a href="test"><b>Fire the bombs!</b></a>
      </aside>
    </turbo-frame>
    <turbo-frame id="frame2"><aside>War never changes</aside></turbo-frame>
  </section>
</main>
